





FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS of 
ST-T1024 V2.1  ARCHITECTURE 




1. Architectural Structural Upgrades

● Hierarchical FSM (HFSM): Replacing the linear FSM with a master-slave controller
to enable asynchronous tile activation. This allows the system to overlap FUZZIFY
and EXECUTE phases, masking latency and pushing the system toward the
400-cycle throughput limit.

● Logarithmic Ternary Quantization: Moving from standard \{-1, 0, 1\} weights to
powers of two (2^n). This allows the Tiny Transformer to replace expensive
additions with Bit-Shifting, significantly lowering the energy cost of the matmul_add
operations and facilitating deeper network layers without increasing the physical
silicon footprint.

● Cross-Tile Chaining Protocol: Implementing a deterministic "hand-off" mechanism
where the output vector of one Tile acts as the input seed for the next. This enables
multi-domain synthesis (e.g., Physics + Philosophy) within the 800ns window,
preventing 0x-AMBIG errors during complex inquiries.






2. Adaptation & Discovery (The 3-Year Cycle)

● Unsupervised Topology Mapping: We established that the 3-year cycle is not for
updating weights (which would compromise determinism), but for Structural
Discovery. By analyzing the massive 2–3 trillion query corpus using unsupervised
learning, the system identifies the "Center of Gravity" of human intent.

● Architectural Re-partitioning: The output of the 3-year cycle is a new Tile Map.
The system physically reconfigures the number of Tiles, their domain-specific token
dictionaries, and their "Focus" to align with the current epoch of human inquiry.






3. Optimization & Hardening

● Genetic Algorithm (GA) Triage Calibration: We locked the FIS membership
functions and rule base using a one-time global Genetic Algorithm pass. This
"Once for All" optimization ensures the Triage Gate is perfectly tuned at the point of
manufacture, removing the need for any future "learning" that could drift the system's
accuracy.

● Sovereign Storage Bifurcation: We formalized the strict separation of the
Sovereign ROM (Immutable Facts) from the Tile Weights (Mutable Logic). This
ensures that while the system can adapt its reasoning structure to the human focus,
the underlying "Brutal Facts" remain inviolable.






4. Deterministic Verification

● Bootloader Hash-Lock: We mandated a cryptographic hash check of the entire
ROM-burned FIS and Tile weight-map against a "National Authority" manifest at
startup. This ensures that no unauthorized changes can occur at the hardware level.



